Lambda is one of the best tools for AWS automation.

Think of AWS Lambda as event-driven automation + short-running compute.

Instead of:
  Going to AWS Console manually ❌
  Clicking buttons every time ❌
  Doing same tasks repeatedly ❌

Lambda automates:
  Detects event → runs automatically ✅
  No human needed ✅
  Runs 24/7 ✅

Lambda + boto3 + CloudWatch cron
= Powerful AWS automation engine

You can automate:
  ✅ Cost saving     (stop unused resources)
  ✅ Security        (find misconfigurations)
  ✅ Backup          (snapshots, exports)
  ✅ Monitoring      (health checks, alerts)
  ✅ Compliance      (audit and fix)
  ✅ Remediation     (auto fix issues)

All without:
  ❌ Managing servers
  ❌ Manual work
  ❌ Human intervention
  ❌ Paying for idle compute

Lambda + boto3 = the most powerful AWS automation combination for DevOps! 🎯
---------

🚀 1. Automation (most common)

Trigger → do task → finish

Stop unused EC2 at night
Start instances in morning
Clean old snapshots / logs
Rotate keys / passwords

👉 Trigger via Amazon EventBridge (cron)



